<p>The Firefox User Panel is an initiative to better understand how people use the Web.  Over 5000 people opted-in to participate in a series of short surveys on a variety of browser-related topics.  The panel represents users from a range of backgrounds and skill sets who are willing to give feedback on their Web experiences.</p>

<p><a href="http://is4.instantsurvey.com/Report/ViewReport.isp?SurveyId=27399&ReportId=10358&iid=105913&uid=6336&lang=en-us&h=TCV4xjwWPCVfhTu3d_8vVw">Results</a> from the first survey are now available.  We hope the data is useful and beneficial for the Mozilla community.  Keep checking here to see what's happening with the Firefox User Panel!</p>

