<h3 id="q1">How do I become a part of the panel?</h3>

<p>We are no longer recruiting for the Firefox User Panel. Thanks to everyone who signed up, we're very excited to work with you!  There are also still plenty of ways to <a href="http://www.spreadfirefox.com/">help Firefox</a> and contribute to the health of the Web.</p>

 

<h3 id="q2">Will I be spammed by Mozilla or anyone else by giving my email address?</h3>

<p>No. We asked you for a valid email address to prevent automated responses to the survey and to inform you about new surveys as they become available.  Of course, you always have the option to opt-out at anytime.  Still concerned?  See the <a href="http://userpanel.mozilla.com/privacy-policy.html">Firefox User Panel Privacy Policy</a> for more details.</p>

 

<h3 id="q3">What if I signed up and then change my mind?</h3>

<p>If you change your mind about participating, you have a few different options.  You can choose not to answer the first survey, which will automatically unsubscribe you from all future surveys or you can unsubscribe by <a href="mailto:firefoxsurvey@mozilla.com?subject=Firefox User Panel - Unsubscribe">emailing us directly</a>.  All future surveys will allow you to opt-out of the User Panel as well.  You can opt-out of a single future survey by simply not taking the survey.</p>

 

<h3 id="q4">What if I never received my invitation email?  Can I still be a part of the panel?</h3>

<p>If you signed up, but never received the invitation email please <a href="mailto:firefoxsurvey@mozilla.com?subject=Firefox User Panel - Subscribe">let us know</a> and we will send the invitation email out to you.</p>

 

<h3 id="q5">If I took the first survey, am I automatically a part of the Firefox User Panel?</h3>

<p>Yes, but we won't ask everyone to take every survey.  We want to make sure we send out surveys that are most relevant for you.  Additionally, we want to make sure we get a diverse mix of respondents for the User Panel, so if we have enough people like you (although of course, there really is no one like you!) we may not need you to take all of the surveys immediately.  Again, if you decide you don't want to be a part of the User Panel after taking the first survey you will have an option to opt-out of the User Panel on any of the following surveys.  You can also <a href="mailto:firefoxsurvey@mozilla.com?subject=Firefox User Panel - Unsubscribe">let us know</a> and we'll remove you from the User Panel.</p>

 

<h3 id="q6">What will happen with the information that is collected?</h3>

<p>Information from the surveys will be used exclusively in the aggregate. The <a href="http://is4.instantsurvey.com/Report/ViewReport.isp?SurveyId=27399&ReportId=10358&iid=105913&uid=6336&lang=en-us&h=TCV4xjwWPCVfhTu3d_8vVw">results from the Firefox User Panel initial survey</a> (excluding all private information) and future results will be available online.  We hope that this data is helpful to the entire Mozilla community.</p>

